cs.PL, cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.LO, cs.SE 

The paper presents a tool for the verification of programs built on top of replicated databases, which involves aspects of programming languages (cs.PL), databases (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), logic (cs.LO), and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of the Why3 framework also suggests a focus on formal methods and program verification, which further supports the likelihood of cs.PL and cs.LO.
